                <h2>iCloud sync</h2>
                <p>
                    Data is stored locally and may sync through Apple iCloud/CloudKit private database services if iCloud is enabled for the app and your device settings allow it. Sync timing and availability can depend on Apple account, network, storage, and device state.
                </p>

                <h2>Share Extension</h2>
                <p>
                    The Share Extension can help add text, URLs, and PDFs from other apps. If a shared item does not appear as expected, check that Curiosity Tracker is enabled in the iOS share sheet and try opening the main app after sharing.
                </p>

                <h2>PDF import</h2>
                <p>
                    PDFs shared into the app may be stored locally or in app storage, and may sync through iCloud if sync is enabled. Large files may take longer to appear across devices.
                </p>

                <h2>Notifications</h2>
                <p>
                    Reminder notifications are optional. You can manage notification permission and delivery from iOS Settings.
                </p>

                <h2>Siri and Shortcuts</h2>
                <p>
                    App Intents and Siri Shortcuts can be used to add curiosities when configured by you. If a shortcut stops working, review it in the Shortcuts app and confirm Curiosity Tracker remains installed.
                </p>

                <h2>Deleting app data</h2>
                <p>
                    You can delete curiosities inside the app. If iCloud sync is enabled, deletion may also sync through iCloud. You can also manage app data through your device and iCloud settings.
                </p>
            </article>
